## Results

The SVM classifier achieved **~98% accuracy** on the test set, correctly classifying 44 out of 45 test samples. GridSearchCV explored 16 combinations of `C` and `gamma` but did not improve on the default model â€” the Iris dataset is small and well-separated, leaving little room for tuning gains.

| Model | Accuracy |
|---|---|
| Default `SVC()` | ~98% |
| GridSearch-tuned SVC | ~98% |

The most separable class is **Iris-setosa**, which forms a clearly distinct cluster in the pairplot. The remaining misclassifications occur between *versicolor* and *virginica*, which overlap slightly in feature space.

